Katherine &quot;Katie&quot; McGirr was eight when she survived exposure during an 1888 blizzard, blind and deaf.  Two years later she was admitted to the New York Institute for the Deaf.  She's mentioned by name in Helen Keller's &quot;The Story of My Life.&quot;
